	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>Few things...</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Aug 25th 12:40 PM 2000</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=353><span id=Sage>Tehom</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>142 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.55]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Keep in mind that the casting time of our charms increases with each additional charm we get. With charm and beguile, you can do a stun, move away, and charm. Higher level ones require you to either root or mesmerize/AE mez one to get it. <br><br>I think that keeping a green or low blue permanently charmed may not be a bad idea, provided you get small pulls. If you get consistently fairly large pulls, why not just charm one of the incoming? It removes a target and still adds the damage you have by keeping a pet from previous fights.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
