	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I also use charm to save lives. For example, if you see some idiot running and yelling for help, charm the mob that is on them. Instantly they are saved from being beat to a bloody pulp. Also charm can teach all those kill stealers a lesson. For instance if there is a wizard using his powerful dd's and stealing your mobs all you do is charm the mob! They will waste mana thinking they are killing it, when in fact it's your pet. Soon they are OOM and the charm will wear off. Then you can kill it for exp.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
